para.para.body:
But matrices can do much more than serve organizational purposes: like vectors, matrices of equal size can be added; it is possible to multiply a matrix by a number; and then there is a new operation: whenever the sizes of two matrices 
                  \Mtrx{A}
                and 
                  \Mtrx{B}
                are compatible, the product 
                  \Mtrx{A}\cdot \Mtrx{B}
                is defined.
